Proposed (39.6s): Use when the user wants to file, open, log, raise, or write up a NEW GitHub issue — a feature request, enhancement ask, or bug report — for a rawgentic project, however they phrase it ("open an issue for…", "log a bug…", "file a feature request…", "track this on github", "users keep asking for X"). Trigger whenever the goal is to capture a desired feature or an observed/reproducible bug as a tracked GitHub issue, even when "rawgentic" isn't named. The skill picks the right repo from project config, checks for duplicates, follows the issue template, and verifies referenced code exists. Do NOT use for: implementing, fixing, or coding the change itself; querying, listing, or reading existing issues; reviewing PRs against an issue; or editing issue-template files. Invoke via /create-issue with a description of the feature or bug.

