Proposed (56.1s): Open and file a brand-new GitHub issue. Trigger this whenever the user wants to capture a feature idea, an enhancement, or a bug as a tracked issue — phrasings like "open/log/raise/file an issue", "write up a bug report", "file a feature request", "put it on github", "open a tracked issue for…", "track this", or "users keep asking for X". Works for any codebase, app, service, dashboard, or repo — whether or not one is named, and without needing the word "rawgentic". It drafts a clean, template-conformant issue and creates it on the correct repo. Do NOT use it to actually implement, fix, or code the change; to list, search, or read existing issues; to review a PR against an issue; or to edit issue-template files.

